meta-fsl-ivi, Freescale In-Vehicle Infotainment
=====================================================

This layer's purpose is to add specific Freescale support
for In-Vehicle Infotainment based on GENIVI meta-ivi layer

A distro configuration poky-ivi-systemd: allows a user to enable
Freescale Wayland graphics backend for the Genivi LayerManager.

Layer dependencies
=====================================================

URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/poky
branch: dizzy
revision: 9fc095a439c36014c73b3a8f240afba09fe0e4d7

URI: git://git.yoctoproject.org/meta-fsl-arm
branch: dizzy
revision: 64752fbb49b16cad881a7b4d35fef3f8315a673f

URI: git://git.openembedded.org/meta-ivi
branch: 7.0
revision: 054f6ca8f17c2387d45049db5ac9450efe2f787b

Build Genivi 7.0.2 p1 with Wayland LayerManager backend
=====================================================

1. Source oe-init-build-env

	source oe-init-build-env

2. Add meta-fsl-ivi layer dependency paths to COREBASE/build/conf/bblayers.conf
   in BBLAYERS variable.

3. Set MACHINE ?= "imx6qsabreauto" in COREBASE/build/conf/local.conf

4. Add INCOMPATIBLE_LICENSE = "GPLv3" in COREBASE/build/conf/local.conf file.

5. Set DISTRO ?= "poky-ivi-systemd" in COREBASE/build/conf/local.conf file.

6. Accept End User License Agrement to use prebuilt GPU binaries
   add in COREBASE/build/conf/local.conf

	ACCEPT_FSL_EULA = "1"

7. Build intrepid-image including GENIVI 7.0.2 P1 components and Wayland backend

	bitbake intrepid-image

Running Wayland test applications
=====================================================

1. Deploy rootfs image into and sdcard

	sudo dd if=intrepid-image-imx6qsabreauto.sdcard of=/dev/SDxx && sync && sync

2. Place SD on imx6sabreauto and power on

3. Start LayerManager

	systemctl start layermanager.service

4. Run test application

	EGLVFBMockNavigation &
